==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fugleman
<hw>Fu"gle*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Fuglemen</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[G.
<ets>fl⟦uum⟧gelmann</ets> file leader; <ets>fl⟦uum⟧gel</ets> wing (akin
to E. fly) + <ets>mann</ets> man. Cf. <er>Flugrelman</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A soldier especially expert and well
drilled, who takes his place in front of a military company, as a guide
for the others in their exercises; a file leader. He originally stood in
front of the right wing.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>flugelman</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, one who leads the way.</def>
<mark>[Jocose]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fugue</ent>⟦br⟧
